irus is|first=Garreth|last=MacNamee|website=TheJournal.ie}}</ref>\n\nThe pandemic's arrival affected many aspects of society, initially including the cancellation of [[Saint Patrick's Day|St Patrick's Day]] parades and all festivals.<ref name=\"Dublin Live Pat Parade canc\"/><ref name=\"Waterford Live Pat canc\"/><ref name=\"Echo parade canc\"/><ref name=\"BBC pat parades off\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51806551|title=Irish St Patrick's Day parades off over coronavirus|date=2020-03-09|publisher=[[BBC News]] |language=en-GB |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]] broke from a trip to [[Washington, D.C.]]\u2014where he was meeting with [[President of the United States]] [[Donald Trump]]\u2014to announce the closure of all schools, colleges, childcare and other public facilities until at least 29 March 2020.<ref name=\"Irish Times schools to shut\"/> These [[public health]] measures were subsequently expanded and extended until at least 19 April 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thejournal.ie/coronavirus-new-measures-5055686-Mar2020/|title=Taoiseach announces all non-essential shops to close, restrictions on gatherings of more than four people|last=Murray|first=Sean|website=[[TheJournal.ie]]|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> [[Leo Varadkar|Varadkar]], a [[physician]], rejoined the [[Medical Council of Ireland|medical register]] to offer his services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/taoiseach-rejoins-medical-register-as-doctor-5067127-Apr2020/|title=Taoiseach Leo Varadkar has registered again as a doctor to help out during Covid-19|last=Dwyer|first=Orla|website=TheJournal.ie|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> \n\n[[President of Ireland]] [[Michael D. Higgins]] signed into law [[Health (Preservation and Protection and other Emergency Measures in the Public Interest) Act 2020|an emergency bill]]\u2014which had earlier passed through [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann|D\u00e1il]] and [[Seanad \u00c9ireann]]\u2014giving the state the power to [[Detention (imprisonment)|detain]] people, restrict travel and keep people in their homes in order to restrict the pandemic.<ref name=\"RTE Higgins signs emerg\"/>\n\n<!-- Please also update the stats in the Europe page also https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe#Ireland -->\nAs of 5 April, there have been 4,994 confirmed cases and 158 deaths.<ref name=\"5 April\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/death-toll-ireland-coronavirus-5066991-Apr2020/|title=Coronavirus: 21 more deaths and 390 new cases confirmed in Ireland|work=[[TheJournal.ie]]|first=Sean|last=Murray|date=5 April 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=500\n|colors=#FF4500,#A50026,#f1f527\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=29 Feb,1 Mar,2 Mar,3 Mar,4 Mar,5 Mar,6 Mar,7 Mar,8 Mar,9 Mar,10 Mar,11 Mar,12 Mar,13 Mar,14 Mar,15 Mar,16 Mar,17 Mar,18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar,21 Mar,22 Mar,23 Mar,24 Mar,25 Mar,26 Mar,27 Mar,28 Mar,29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar,1 Apr,2 Apr,3 Apr,4 Apr,5 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=Cases\n|y1Title=Total confirmed cases\n|y1=1,1,1,2,6,13,18,19,21,24,34,43,70,90,129,169,223,292,366,557,683,785,906,1125,1329,1564,1819,2121,2415,2615,2910,3235,3447,3849,4273,4604,4994\n|y2=,,,,,,,,,,,1,1,1,2,2,2,2,2,3,3,3,4,6,7,9,19,22,36,46,54,71,85,98,120,137,158\n|y3=,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,59,84,114,147,159,208,247,283,321,375,445,506,578,674,752,841,948,1084,1163\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n{{legend|#FF4500|Total Confirmed Cases.\n{{legend|#f1f527|Total healthcare worker confirmed cases.\n{{legend|#A50026|Total Deaths.\n}}}}}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=500\n|colors=#FF4500,#000000,#87CEEB\n|type=stackedrect\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=29 Feb,1 Mar,2 Mar,3 Mar,4 Mar,5 Mar,6 Mar,7 Mar,8 Mar,9 Mar,10 Mar,11 Mar,12 Mar,13 Mar,14 Mar,15 Mar,16 Mar,17 Mar,18 Mar,19 Mar,20 Mar,21 Mar,22 Mar,23 Mar,24 Mar,25 Mar,26 Mar,27 Mar,28 Mar,29 Mar,30 Mar,31 Mar,1 A