rvices] {{in lang|ar}}\n*[http://www.tishreen.edu.sy{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Tishreen University]{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} {{in lang|en|ar}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090124044737/http://www.ulivewhere.com/low/downloads/download-latakia.html Audio interview with Latakia resident about life in Latakia] \n*[http://www.pbase.com/dosseman_syria/latakia Pictures from 2009]\n*{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Latakia|short=x}}\n\n{{Coord|35|31|N|35|47|E|region:SY_type:city|display=title}}\n\n{{Cities of Syria}}{{Latakia Governorate|latakia}}\n{{Mediterranean Games}}\n{{Hellenistic colonies}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Latakia| ]]\n[[Category:Levant]]\n[[Category:Cities in Syria]]\n[[Category:Seleucid colonies]]\n[[Category:Phoenician cities]]\n[[Category:Roman sites in Syria]]\n[[Category:Port cities in Asia]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean port cities and towns in Syria]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in the 2nd millennium BC]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Syria]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|Latakia city|the governorate|Latakia Governorate|other uses}}\n{{more citations needed|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          = Latakia\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            = {{lang|ar|\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0627\u0630\u0642\u064a\u0629}}<!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \"Bride of the Mediterranean\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://syriatimes.sy/index.php/tourism/22859-meshquita-treasure-trove-of-sparkling-springs-and-lush-forests|title=Meshquita; treasure trove of sparkling springs and lush forests|last=Hamsa|date=|website=syriatimes.sy|accessdate=27 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180102073735/http://syriatimes.sy/index.php/tourism/22859-meshquita-treasure-trove-of-sparkling-springs-and-lush-forests|archive-date=2 January 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|settlement_type        = City\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = {{Photomontage\n| photo1a                   = Lattakia beach (335105386).jpg{{!}}Beach\n| photo2a                   = Lazkiye Suriye - panoramio.jpg{{!}}The governor's palace\n| photo2b                   = Latakia harbour.jpg{{!}}The city's harbour\n| photo3a                   = Museum of Latakia, Syria.jpg{{!}}Latakia Museum\n| photo3b                   = Al assad stadium latakia.jpg{{!}}Al-Assad Stadium\n| photo4a                   = Latakia Sports City aerial view in 1991.jpg{{!}}Latakia Sports City\n| spacing                   = 2\n| position                  = center\n| color_border              = white\n| color                     =  white\n| size                      = 266\n| foot_montage              = \n}}\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             =\n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = Latakia - Seal.jpg\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              =\n|mapsize                =\n|map_caption            =\n|image_map1             =\n|mapsize1               =\n|map_caption1           =\n|image_dot_map          =\n|dot_mapsize            =\n|dot_map_caption        =\n|dot_x =  |dot_y =\n|pushpin_map            = Syria#Asia\n|pushpin_label_position = left\n|pushpin_relief           = yes\n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Latakia within Syria\n<!-- Location ------------------>\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name       = {{SYR}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Governorates of Syria|Governorate]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Latakia Governorate]]\n|subdivision_type2 